andi
------------------------------------------
This is the andi program for estimating the evolutionary distance between
closely related genomes. These distances can be used to rapidly infer
phylogenies for big sets of genomes. Because andi does not compute full
alignments, it is so efficient that it scales even up to thousands of bacterial
genomes.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.0-0.450.g2ef627c46eb2
  libdivsufsort3-2.0.1-1bl3
  libgcc1-11.4.0-1
  libgomp1-11.4.0-1
  libgsl19-2.3-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.41-3
  cygport-0.36.7-1
  gcc-core-11.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.4.0-1
  libdivsufsort-devel-2.0.1-1bl3
  libgsl-devel-2.3-2
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/EvolBioInf/andi

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/EvolBioInf/andi/archive/refs/tags/v0.14.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack andi-0.14-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./andi-0.14-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/andi-0.14-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/andi-0.14-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(andi)
  /usr/bin/andi.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/andi.README
  /usr/share/doc/andi/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/andi/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/andi/andi-manual.pdf
  /usr/share/man/man1/andi.1.gz

